obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (29718)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application, commencement, duration and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29718&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be`
  line `called the National Commission for Safai Karamcharis Act, 1993.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line
  line `(4) It shall cease to have effect after the ^3[29th day of February, 2004], except as respects things done`
  line `or omitted to be done before such cesser, and upon such cesser section 6 of the General Clauses Act,`
  line `1897 (10 of 1897), shall apply as if this Act had then been repealed by a Central Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
  line
  line `2. 12th August, 1994, vide notification No. S.O. 591(E), dated 12th August, 1994, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 55 of 2001, s.2, for "31st day of March, 2002" (w.e.f. 13-12-2001)`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (29719)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29719&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commission" means the National Commission for Safai Karamcharis constituted under`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Member" means a Member of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "Safai Karamchari" means a person engaged in, or employed for, manually carrying human`
  line `excreta or any sanitation work;`
  line
  line `(f) "Vice-Chairperson" means the Vice-Chairperson of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (29720)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the National Commission for Safai Karamcharis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29720&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a body to be known as the National`
  line `Commission for Safai Karamcharis to exercise the powers conferred on, and to perform the functions`
  line `assigned to, it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of --`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) a Vice-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) fiveMembers,`
  line
  line `to be nominated, from amongst the persons of eminence connected with the socio-economic development`
  line `and welfare of Safai Karamcharis, by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that at least one of the Members shall be a woman.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (29721)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29721&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and every Member shall hold office for such period`
  line `not exceeding three years as may be specified by the Central Government in this behalf or up to the 31st`
  line `day of March, 1997, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and every Member holding office as such`
  line `immediately before the commencement of the National Commission for Safai Karamcharis (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1997 (18 of 1997)shall vacate their respective offices on the 31st day of March, 1997:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and every Member appointed after the`
  line `commencement of the National Commission for Safai Karamcharis (Amendment) Act, 1997 (18 of 1997)`
  line `shall hold office for such period not exceeding three years as may be specified by the Central Government`
  line `in this behalf or up to the 31st day of March, 2002, whichever is earlier.]`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and`
  line `every Member appointed on or after the 16th day of February, 2001, shall hold office for a period not`
  line `exceeding three years from the date of assumption of his office or up to the 29th day of February, 2004,`
  line `whichever is earlier.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson or a Member may, by notice in writing addressed to the`
  line `Central Government, resign from the office of Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson, or as the case may be, of`
  line `the Member at any time.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall remove a person from the office of Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson`
  line `or a Member if that person--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) is convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, involves moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(c) becomes of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(d) refuses to act or becomes incapable of acting;`
  line
  line `(e) is, without obtaining leave of absence from the Commission, absent from three consecutive`
  line `meetings of the Commission; or`
  line
  line `(f) in the opinion of the Central Government has so abused the position of Chairperson,`
  line `Vice-Chairperson or Member as to render that persons continuance in office detrimental to the public`
  line `interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be removed under this clause until that person has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(4) A vacancy caused under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or otherwise shall be filled by fresh`
  line `nomination and a person so nominated shall hold office for the unexpired period of the term for which his`
  line `predecessor in office would have held office if such vacancy had not arisen.`
  line
  line `(5) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and Members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1997, s.3 (w.e.f 25-3-1997).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 55 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 13-12-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (29722)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Officers and other employees of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29722&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall provide`
  line `the Commission with such officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient performance of`
  line `the functions of the Commission under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the officers`
  line `and other employees appointed for the purpose of the Commission shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (29723)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vacancy, etc., not to invalidate the proceedings of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29723&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of`
  line `the Commission shall be questioned or shall be invalid on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (29724)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Procedure to be regulated by the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29724&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall meet as and when`
  line `necessary and shall meet at such time and place as the Chairperson may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(3) All orders and decisions of the Commission shall be authenticated by the Chairperson or any other`
  line `officer of the Commission duly authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (29725)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions and powers of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29725&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall perform all or any of the`
  line `following functions namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) recommend to the Central Government specific programmes of action towards elimination of`
  line `inequalities in status, facilities and opportunities for Safai Karamcharis under a time-bound action`
  line plan;
  line
  line `(b) study and evaluate the implementation of the programmes and schemes relating to the social`
  line `and economic rehabilitation of Safai Karamcharis and make recommendations to the Central`
  line `Government and State Governments for better co-ordination and implementation of such programmes`
  line `and schemes;`
  line
  line `(c) investigate specific grievances and take suo moto notice of matters relating to`
  line `non-implementation of--`
  line
  line `(i) programmes or schemes in respect of any group of Safai Karamcharis;`
  line
  line `(ii) decisions, guidelines or instructions, aimed at mitigating the hardship of Safai`
  line Karamcharis;
  line
  line `(iii) measures for the social and economic up liftment of Safai Karamcharis;`
  line
  line `(iv) the provisions of any law in its application to Safai Karamcharis,`
  line
  line `and take up such matters with the concerned authorities or with the Central or State Governments;`
  line
  line `(d) make periodical reports to the Central and State Governments on any matter concerning Safai`
  line `Karamcharis, taking into account any difficulties or disabilities being encountered by Safai`
  line Karamcharis;
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which may be referred to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In the discharge of its functions under sub-section (1), the Commission shall have power to call`
  line `for information with respect to any matter specified in that sub-section from any Government or local or`
  line `other authority`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (38026)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and Members and staff of the Commission to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=38026&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson, Members, officers and other employees of the`
  line `Commission shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (29726)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Central Government to consult Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29726&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall consult the`
  line `Commission on all major policy matters affecting Safai Karamcharis.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (29727)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29727&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall prepare in such form and at such time for each financial`
  line `year as may be prescribed its annual report giving a full account of its activities during the previous`
  line `financial year and forward a copy thereof to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (29728)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Annual report to be laid before Parliament or the Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29728&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall cause the annual report to be laid before each House of Parliament along with the`
  line `memorandum explaining the action taken or proposed to be taken on the recommendations contained`
  line `therein in so far as they relate to the Central Government and the reasons for non-acceptance, if any, of`
  line `any such recommendation.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the said report or any part thereof relates to any matter with which a State Government is`
  line `concerned, a copy of such report shall be forwarded to the Governor of the State who shall cause it to be`
  line `laid before the Legislature of the State along with a memorandum explaining the action taken or proposed`
  line `to be taken on the recommendations relating to the State and the reasons for the non-acceptance, if any, of`
  line `any such recommendation or part.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (29729)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29729&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Commission may, by general or special order, delegate to the`
  line `Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson or any Member or to any officer of the Commission subject to such`
  line `conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified therein, such of its powers and duties under this`
  line `Act as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (29730)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29730&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, Commission, Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson, Members or any officer`
  line `or other employee of the Commission for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (29731)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969&sectionId=29731&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00003_199364_1517807322969
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:-`
  line
  line `(a) salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and Members under sub-section (5) of section 4 and of officers and`
  line `other employees of the Commission under sub-section (2) of section5;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in, and the time at, which the annual report shall be prepared under section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
